%% Diagram: Routing query data flow (CH + live traffic overlay)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant API as API Gateway
    participant Router as Routing Service (CH)
    participant Graph as CH Graph (mmap)
    participant Traffic as Traffic Store (TSDB)
    participant Geo as Geocoder

    Client->>API: POST /routes {origin, destination, depart_at}
    API->>Geo: snap origin/destination to nearest road node
    Geo-->>API: (node_src, node_dst)
    API->>Router: route(node_src, node_dst, depart_at)

    par fetch base graph
        Router->>Graph: bidirectional upward Dijkstra
    and overlay live traffic
        Router->>Traffic: speed multipliers for candidate edges
        Traffic-->>Router: per-segment multipliers (1–5 min window)
    end

    Router->>Router: edge_weight = base_weight x multiplier
    Router->>Router: meet at top node, unpack shortcuts
    Router-->>API: polyline + per-step ETAs
    API-->>Client: route(s) + duration_in_traffic

    Note over Router,Traffic: Topology never changes at query time — traffic is a multiplier on the static CH graph
